        

        Basic Commands

1 . to create project - ng new project-name / ng new project-name --routing

2 . to run a project - ng serve / ng serve --open

3 . to create a component - ng g c component-name



         Basic Concepts

1 . component - to create {html,css,ts file} root component - AppComponent

2 . Module - to add libraries to the project - root module - AppModule

3 . Data Binding - data sharing between html to ts 
   
   3.1 One way Binding
     
     3.1.1 Component to view
         
         3.1.1.1 String Interpolation: syntax - {{variable-name}}

         3.1.1.2 Property Binding: syntax - [attribute]="variable-name" 
     
     3.1.2 view to component 

         3.1.2.1 Evevt Binding - (evet)="function-call()"

         3.1.2.2 Evevt Binding Using $event - (evet)="function-call($event)"

         3.1.2.3 Template Referencing Variable - syntax :- #variable - name


    3.2 Two Way Binding

        3.2.1 using ngModel - Import FormsModule in AppModule  


 4 . To setup path for a component : defined in App Routing Module

    syntax :- {path:'',component : componentClassName}  

 5 . Dependency Injection - to share data between classes    

 6 . Angular Dependancy - for redundant data 

 7 . ngSubmit - to submit entire form 
         
         syntax :- (ngSubmit)="function-call"

 8 . Angular Forms

      8.1 Template Driven Forms - first design html

      8.2 Model Driven Forms - first create model in ts

          8.2.1 Reactive Forms - Add Validation: Import ReactiveFormsModule
                         - form group - FormBuilder dependency inject,form array,form control
                     
               
                 
            




          
        